article.headline: Florida A&M 74, Savannah St. 65
article.story: HOFFMAN ESTATES, Ill. (AP) -- Darius Glover and Rome Sanders scored 19 points each to lead Florida A&M to a 74-65 victory over Savannah State on Saturday in the Chicago Invitational Challenge. Leading 61-59 with 1:39 remaining, Florida A&M (2-5) pulled away by outscoring Savannah State 7-0. Ernest Maul hit two free throws for Florida A&M to put the Rattlers up 68-59 with 28.5 seconds left. Jon Mason was perfect from the line making all eight free throw attempts and finished with 12 points for Florida A&M, and Joe Ballard added 11 points. Javon Randolph led Savannah State (5-3) with 20 points and Patrick Hardy scored 11. Florida A&M led 30-28 at the half. Sanders scored 11 points in the first half for Florida A&M.
